genresAdvancedInfo.name: chilean techno
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Chilean techno is a genre of electronic dance music that originated in Chile and is characterized by its dark, minimalistic sound. It often features heavy basslines, distorted synths, and repetitive beats, with influences from techno, house, and industrial music. Chilean techno is known for its underground scene and experimental approach to music production.
